dct_title_s: Map of the Cocos or Keeling Islands, exhibiting the changes that have taken place since 1836
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by hachures. Depth shown by soundings and isobaths. Shoals, sand bars, and channels through shallow areas are shown. "The outline & remarks printed in black is a reduction of the Admiralty chart published in 1866. The changes that have occurred, as delineated by Mr. Forbes, 1879, are marked in Red." Area of poisoned water, January 1876, is shown. Includes insets: North Island [showing North Keeling to scale] -- General map showing the relative position of the islands [scale ca. 1:733,000], showing sand spits between North and South islands. From: Proceedings of the Royal Geographical Society and monthly record of geography. Vol. 1 (1879), no. 12, pp. 777-84; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J6873
